steel - Light view for German steel industry
the crisis @-@ battered and energy @-@ intensive German steel industry remains spared millions of additional costs .
financial burdens that have threatened the industry from oil production are off the table .
it remains in the liberation from the Renewable Energy levy on inventories for so @-@ called own electricity production in the German steel industry , said Federal Minister Sigmar Gabriel ( SPD ) of the Westdeutsche Allgemeine Zeitung ( WAZ , Friday &apos;s edition ) .
&quot; I &apos;m really glad that after two years of tough negotiations we were finally able to achieve that . &quot;
the European Commission had therefore initially planned to ask the steel manufacturers who use gases from the hoop to produce electricity for their own consumption .
according to the German trade association , the steel industry threatened an additional cost of 120 to 240 million euros a year .
Gabriel told the WAZ there is now a keynote agreement with the EU Commission following talks with Competition Commissioner Margrethe Vestager .
only when the generators are replaced in the steel plants will an EEG levy of 20 percent .
but this is not raised in the steel industry either .
the IG Metal welcomed Germany &apos;s agreement with the EU Commission on own @-@ energy production .
this largely enshrines the status quo of the existing system .
Gabriel &apos;s success in the steel industry is particularly important .
&quot; in terms of our &quot; Steel campaign , &quot; this is a first step . &quot;
&quot; others have to follow . &quot;
&quot; climate and employment objectives must also be weighed up in the reform of the emissions trading regime , &quot; said IG Metal Chief JÃ¶rg Hofmann in Frankfurt .
the steel industry in Europe has been suffering from overcapacity and significant price pressures since the 2008 financial crisis .
last year , the situation continued to deteriorate as the world &apos;s largest producer country , China , threw mass steel onto the world market in the face of weakening domestic demand .
European producers accuse Chinese steel companies of price dumping .
in the course of this spring , the situation has eased somewhat .
on the one hand , import duties imposed on imported steel are showing an impact , and on the other hand , the economic outlook in China has hung up .
it is unclear how sustainable the price recovery is .
German industry primary Thyssenkrupp remained cautious on Thursday .
most recently , prices would have stagnated again .
the industry is responding to the difficult situation with further cost cuts .
ThyssenKrupp did not want to rule out closures of individual works .
around 86000 people were employed in the German steel industry at the end of 2015 .
in July , German steel manufacturers remain cautious despite rising prices and increasing orders .
they produced well six per cent less crude at 3.4 million tonnes than in the previous year , according to economic union Steel reported Friday .
after a brief increase in May , the produced crowd now declined for the second month in a row .
since the beginning of the year , production has been two per cent below the previous year .
in the coming months , the Association expects to see an increase in its order position .
community , spirit , health : singing does senior people well
singing has already accompanied Ursel Kipp all her life : as a young girl she was in school choir , in the Lehramt studies she lectured the compartment music , and today the 78 @-@ year @-@ old sings in a senior choir .
&quot; singing moves me - emotionally and physically , &quot; she describes .
after a sample , she feels balanced , cheerful and overall alive , she says .
by the way , she does something good about her health and spirit .
because singing is a great hobby for seniors right from several perspectives , says Erhard Hackler of the German senior league .
most seniors sing in the choir and share with peers the joy of music , describes Hackler .
through regular coexistence , seniors can establish and maintain social contacts .
because social and family structures often solve at age , a choir is then an ideal opportunity to spend time with other people .
this experience has also made Ursel Kipp in her chorus : &quot; take off and organize , rely on the others and learn from each other - a choir is a very special form of coexistence . &quot;
singing can be exhausting in the positive sense , says Hackler .
because seniors are training deep and controlled breathing .
those who regularly demand their lungs do not get out of the puste in everyday life .
even when it comes to getting the sound of voice at age , singing is an optimal hobby .
on older people , Singen often has a very special effect , says Ursula Lenz of the federal Labor Association of senior organizations .
in the older generations , the common singing was much higher , it belonged to everyday life , both in school and leisure , she explains .
Lenz often observed that singing or listening to songs in older people awakens many memories , often associated with positive feelings of her youth time .
through lyrics and especially melodies , self @-@ dementia sufferers escape long @-@ running events .
when singing , the head is also required to perform a special performance , Lenz explains .
at the same time , concentrate on your own voice and on a given rhythm , adapting to the other singers - that is a great cognitive challenge .
older people who live alone practice not just to focus on themselves .
another positive aspect is the recognition obtained by singing in the choir , says Hackler .
an enthusiastic audience is a great praise .
self @-@ esteem is also growing by singing in the choir .
to show yourself : if I go for something for a long time , I get better and wake up beyond me - this experience strengthens .
good reasons to start singing , then there is enough .
anyone who wants to try a new hobby should not hesitate - even if he thinks he has little talent , Lenz advises .
you don &apos;t sing alone - at 50 singing people , who is listening when a sound goes next ?
looking for the appropriate offer , seniors have different options , Hackler says .
singing someone from the acquaintance in a senior choir can easily be joined .
many cities also offer views of the ChÃ¶re area .
anyone who wants to sing in a church choir can contact the community or the church front directly .
many senior places are also found via the Internet .
anyone who does not have access to the Internet can ask the family , friends or neighbours for help from the Internet .
anyone who wants to sing should definitely join a choir , Hackler advises .
singing does the soul well and has something liberating - that applies to every age .
cats react more sensitively than hangover on cries of young animals
biologists have studied in Hanover the effect of running cat babies on adult animals .
to their surprise , this didn &apos;t make the males cold either - but they kept the same in contrast to the females .
female cats can recognize Katzenbaby &apos;s grazing degree .
they respond by 10 per cent faster to Laute of kittens who choose to be in great need , as scientists from the Veterinary University and the Medical University of Hanover ( MHH ) found .
hangovers also respond to the calls of kittens - but always equal .
&quot; obviously , the acoustic differences between mistrust of less and heavily razed juveniles for the males are either not perceptible or not relevant , &quot; said biologist Wiebke Konerding of the MHH .
she is a graduate of the study , published this Friday in the journal BMC Evolutionary Biology .
in a previous investigation , the research team had already found that the duration and pitch of the kittens were different from the urgency of their need for help .
a total of nine adult hangovers and eight kittens from the MHH &apos;s livestock were observed .
they were presented for one run of little ones , taken from the root box for three minutes and separated by mother and siblings .
on the other hand , they were confronted with chills of more razed kittens , which were additionally raised .
the researchers consider their results to be meaningful despite the low sample .
&quot; all females , even those who haven &apos;t had their own offspring , responded differentially to the cries , &quot; Konerding said .
they turned faster to the loudspeaker when this call of the very rainy kittens played off .
this ability may be innate or evolve with the gender maturity .
&quot; one surprise was that the males responded at all , &quot; the biologist said .
in the past , scientists have repeatedly examined the reactions of women and men to baby noise .
some studies also showed that women were more sensitive to babies , whether or not they were mothers , the biologist Marina Scheumann reported .
