condoms with Chilipuder , fireworks promote dance anias elephant protection
conservationists in Tanzania use an unorthodox way to prevent elephants from going in people @-@ owned settlements - they throw condoms on them filled with chilipuder .
the method has proved effective and the Honeyguide Foundation , which had the idea of doing so years ago , has stepped up its promotion along with U.S. nature conservation by training volunteers in villages in northern Tanzania , using a non @-@ violent four @-@ stage method to protect their homes and crops without violating animals .
previously , many spears used to defend themselves .
Friday is world telephone day dedicated to animal welfare .
&quot; since we developed the ... toolkit , we have been able to observe a change of attitude within these communities , which are much more confident that they can discourage elephants from their fields without harming the elephants , &quot; Honeyguide &apos;s managing director Damian Bell said in a note .
the first two steps include lighting the elephant with a torch and blowing into a horn .
if he is not deterred , a so @-@ called &quot; Chiliwolke &quot; is thrown .
chilipuder milled with earth is packed together with a fireworks body into a condom whose end is turned up to the ignition .
when it is lit , the condom bursts with a bang and spits fine dust to chilipuder into the air .
a hint quite usually already out to chase the elephant .
one last option is a scorcher who shoots a gold @-@ fired plant into the air , causing a loud , bright explosion .
