Honda HR @-@ V is flexible and everyday
in the small HR @-@ V Honda wants to pack everything : a little SUV , a little coupÃ© and also the versatility of a minivans .
sounds quite overloaded , but the HR @-@ V , constructed on the same new platform as the new jazz , is actually proving to be very flexible in everyday life .
although the only 1.60 m high HR @-@ V looks rather small , passengers have plenty of space in both the front row and the rear , it doesn &apos;t work closely at all .
the interior materials are well processed and look pleasant , only the cockpit upper side falls off there .
the HR @-@ V is more versatile than comparable vehicles .
it is not only a trunk of 453 l at high @-@ level and 1026 l at converted backrests , but there are the Magic Seats .
this is less magical than it sounds : the seat areas of the backbench can be mounted like cinema chairs , thus providing storage space that is 1.24 m high from the ground to the ceiling .
the boot can be loaded well , but the loading height of 650 mm is slightly higher than the comparable Peugeot 2008 .
the 1.6 @-@ litre diesel tested with 88 kW / 120 horsepower accelerates the HR @-@ V thanks to the torque of up to 300 Nm in wide speed ranges .
he is likely to do his job somewhat quieter .
the daily consumption of 4.7 l / 100 km is pleasing .
there is another motorization : a 1.5 @-@ litre petrol station with 96 kW / 130 hp .
an all @-@ wheel drive is not offered .
driving is balanced , a good compromise between dynamism and comfort .
however , the steering is likely to be slightly more direct .
the equipment in the tested top version &quot; Executive &quot; leaves no wishes open .
security systems include the City emergency brake assistant ( working up to speed 32 ) , the collision warning system and the track maintenance assistant .
the collision warner sometimes irritates because he evaluates many obstacles as &quot; approaching objects . &quot;
the remote light assistant works very reliably .
and the intelligent speed controller responds to traffic sign recognition and reduces speed if needed .
full connectivity , however , is available only for the top equipment : 7 @-@ inch touchscreen , Navi , app integration and more .
two USB and an HDMI book are under the arm rest and are therefore somewhat cumbersome .
the roughly 29,000 euros for the well @-@ equipped top diesel are fine .
those who do not want to invest so much will receive the petrol from 20000 euros , the diesel from 23,000 euros .
the engines meet the Euro 6 exhaust standard .
with HR @-@ V , Honda offers a versatile and everyday car .
airline is not liable : fall on passenger bridge
an airline is not liable for the fall of a passenger on the passenger bridge .
because liability is only possible in the event of dangers typical of air transport , the High Court of DÃ¼sseldorf ( Az . : 18 U 124 / 14 ) argued .
the plaintiff had broken a knee strain in the fall .
however , the accident could have happened everywhere - it was a general risk of life , according to the court .
the airline did not have to pay compensation to the man .
disease case : when does the organiser pay
sick holidaymakers only get money back after their journey if the cause of the disease is doubtless found in the hotel .
however , this is only the case if more than 10 percent of guests have shown the same symptoms .
in the negotiated case , a family was seriously ill on the second day of their doorstep .
she spent almost the entire holiday in the room .
her illness attributed holidaymakers to a faulty treatment plant that allegedly polluted sea water .
the family thought the trip was flawed by it - and complained against the organizer .
in court , the plaintiffs had no success .
while the treatment plant was indeed defective .
but the organiser only learned about it just before the plaintiffs &apos; departure .
he had to assume by then that sea water was fine .
so he did not violate his information obligations , according to the ruling .
especially in the samples of water , no contamination was found .
the disease of several hotel guests - possibly through contagion among themselves - is a general risk of life .
of 691 guests , only 38 were ill .
