recovering night : tips against sleep disorders
in the evening you get around forever , at night you get awake , and in the morning you can &apos;t think of sleep well before the Weckerbell .
this is far from relaxing .
after all , such problems are in good society : according to the Robert Koch Institute , about a quarter of adults have sleep disorders and more than 10 percent feel their sleep is frequent or permanent .
how do sleep problems or sleep disturbances ?
there are several forms of sleep disorders , and they can be based on a variety of causes , says Hans @-@ GÃ¼nter WeeÃ , a member of the Management Board of the German Society for Sleep Medicine .
but what you can understand about it is the insomnie , that is , an injunction and sleep disorder .
it is precisely this that many people find unsatisfactory or inadequate , says Jens Wagenknecht , member of the Board of Directors of the German Medical Association with practice in the Dutch Varel .
what &apos;s behind sleep disorders ?
the causes of sleep disorders are complex .
this can contain organic , mental or behavioral factors , but also drugs .
it is not rare that sleep disorder is an expression of another disease .
&quot; very early awakening is common especially in a depression , &quot; WeeÃ says .
and it may be that different factors match each other .
for example , if you have a band failure , you can be bad , wake up every two to three hours and start grinning about everyday problems and concerns , WeeÃ gives an example .
this leads to tension , and sleep is no longer possible .
when should you have sleep problems with a doctor ?
those who don &apos;t sleep well over a period of one month in at least three nights a week and are affected on the day should go to the doctor , wee .
the impairment may look very different : one is cut off , tired , uncut , has difficulties with attention and concentration , is slightly irritable , has mood swings or physical ailments such as stomach or headache .
to alleviate sleep disturbance , it is important to find out their causes .
among other things , behavioral changes , cognitive behavioral therapy , or even drugs - classic sleeping pills only in exceptional cases and at most for two weeks .
there are hardly any established sleep doctors in Germany , emphasizes Prof. Ingo Fietze , head of the interdisciplinary sleep medical center of CharitÃ© University Medicine Berlin .
for this reason , you should first contact the doctor in case of sleep problems .
this can be explained with studies of whether the problems have a physical cause .
who should go to the sleep lab , and what happens ?
in order to study in the sleep lab , physicians advise , for example , in snoring with respiratory agents , in sickbay fatigue , in sleep converters or if you don &apos;t find the cause of a distress disorder , Fietze explains .
we do not really need to prepare for the investigation .
you should spend the day normally .
&quot; just don &apos;t make a lunch sleep , &quot; Fietze says .
after dressing you go to bed at your normal time .
in addition to the electrodes on the body , one wears a nose , a chest belt and a fiber on the finger .
in addition , a camera on the ceiling features the sleeping end .
how can those affected get to grips with the problems ?
there are quite a lot of pitches to be set for a better sleep .
there is a regular sleep and sleep time , not too long in bed , not sleep in the day , not a TV to sleep , drink and not watch the clock at night .
